<i>♪ Heroes in a half shell ♪</i>

00:58.858 --> 01:00.591
<i>♪ Turtle power ♪</i>

01:08.868 --> 01:10.902
Master Splinter,
you have taught me much

01:10.904 --> 01:12.838
about the ways
of the ninja,

01:12.840 --> 01:14.906
but I know that there
is one combat maneuver

01:14.908 --> 01:16.407
you have yet
to teach any of us.

01:18.144 --> 01:19.577
Very well, Leonardo.

01:19.579 --> 01:21.279
I will teach you
the one technique

01:21.281 --> 01:23.281
for which
there is no defense:

01:23.283 --> 01:25.617
the viper maneuver.

01:25.619 --> 01:27.886
The, uh, viper maneuver?

01:27.888 --> 01:29.620
To accomplish this move,

01:29.622 --> 01:32.857
you must first let your
whole spine become flexible,

01:32.859 --> 01:34.226
like a snake's.

01:34.228 --> 01:36.461
This draws your
opponent toward you.

01:36.463 --> 01:40.398
Then you must transform
your spine into solid steel,

01:40.400 --> 01:42.667
striking like a cobra.

01:47.172 --> 01:48.840
Now you try it.

01:48.842 --> 01:50.408
Spine like serpent,

01:50.410 --> 01:52.143
then like steel,

01:52.145 --> 01:54.412
strike!

01:54.414 --> 01:57.982
Ah, I guess I need
a little practice.

01:57.984 --> 02:00.185
Spine like serpent,

02:00.187 --> 02:01.619
then like steel,

02:01.621 --> 02:03.688
strike!

02:05.424 --> 02:08.059
I do not understand,
Leonardo.

02:08.061 --> 02:09.961
You're
my most gifted pupil,

02:09.963 --> 02:12.497
yet this maneuver seems
beyond your ability.

02:12.499 --> 02:15.433
Ah, maybe I'm just
having a bad day.

02:15.435 --> 02:17.435
Perhaps you have
some hidden fear

02:17.437 --> 02:19.838
which prevents you from
accomplishing the maneuver.

02:19.840 --> 02:21.205
What?

02:21.207 --> 02:22.607
That's not true,
Master Splinter.

02:22.609 --> 02:24.242
I'm not afraid
of anything.

02:24.244 --> 02:26.144
If you say so, my pupil,

02:26.146 --> 02:29.080
but you will not be able
to accomplish the viper

02:29.082 --> 02:31.716
until you have faced
your darkest fear

02:31.718 --> 02:34.051
and overcome it.

02:34.053 --> 02:36.821
Leonardo, you're just
in time to check this out.

02:36.823 --> 02:38.823
<i>[April]</i>
<i>Perhaps the most</i>
<i>baffling robbery</i>

02:38.825 --> 02:41.592
<i>in the city's history</i>
<i>was committed yesterday.</i>

02:41.594 --> 02:45.063
<i>Police don't have a clue as</i>
<i>to who the guilty party is,</i>

02:45.065 --> 02:46.698
<i>or why anyone</i>
<i>in their right mind</i>

02:46.700 --> 02:48.366
<i>would commit</i>
<i>such a robbery,</i>

02:48.368 --> 02:50.001
yet as you can see,

02:50.003 --> 02:51.436
every one
of the 600 snakes

02:51.438 --> 02:55.373
in the city zoo's reptile
house has been stolen.

02:55.375 --> 02:57.309
Ah, snakes?

02:57.311 --> 03:00.211
What kind of a nut case
would steal 600 snakes?

03:00.213 --> 03:03.281
Uh, now I'm not in the
mood for television.

03:03.283 --> 03:04.849
Maybe
I'll read a good book.

03:06.686 --> 03:08.954
Hey, that's a good idea,
Leonardo.

03:08.956 --> 03:10.721
Maybe we'll find a clue
about the robbery

03:10.723 --> 03:12.791
in my illustrated
guide to snakes.

03:12.793 --> 03:14.458
On the other hand,

03:14.460 --> 03:16.460
maybe I would
rather watch TV.

03:19.532 --> 03:22.200
It's high time we did these
dishes, Michelangelo.

03:26.405 --> 03:28.573
Aw, major gross-out.

03:28.575 --> 03:30.475
This sink
is stopped up again.

03:32.511 --> 03:33.678
Yo, Donatello,

03:33.680 --> 03:35.312
where'd you put the snake?

03:35.314 --> 03:36.213
S-S-Snake?

03:36.215 --> 03:37.348
There's a snake in here?

03:38.884 --> 03:40.118
Yeah, here it is.

03:40.120 --> 03:41.886
What's the matter
with you, Leonardo,

03:41.888 --> 03:43.555
you're as jumpy
as a cat lately.

03:43.557 --> 03:46.558
Yeah, dude, maybe you
ought to switch to decaf.

03:51.330 --> 03:52.597
Fellow turtles,

03:52.599 --> 03:55.867
this baffling mystery deserves
our undivided attention.

03:55.869 --> 03:57.134
That's right.

03:57.136 --> 03:59.203
Snake lovers everywhere
are counting on us.

03:59.205 --> 04:00.604
<i>What am I going to do?</i>

04:00.606 --> 04:02.573
<i>I'm terrified of snakes,</i>

04:02.575 --> 04:04.909
<i>but the guys look</i>
<i>to me for leadership.</i>

04:04.911 --> 04:06.410
Now, the first
thing we should do

04:06.412 --> 04:08.646
is check out the
snake house for clues.

04:08.648 --> 04:10.582
Hey, guys!

04:10.584 --> 04:12.784
Maybe we should stop
for a slice of pizza.

04:12.786 --> 04:14.685
Not now, dude.

04:14.687 --> 04:17.656
We're hot
on the snake case.

04:17.658 --> 04:20.925
Uh, anyone for hopscotch?

04:22.461 --> 04:24.929
What has gotten into you,
Leonardo?

04:24.931 --> 04:27.265
Yeah, we've got to get
to the bottom of this

04:27.267 --> 04:29.467
baffling disappearing
snake mystery.

04:29.469 --> 04:32.970
Uh, dudes, speaking
of baffling mysteries.

04:36.875 --> 04:39.177
Uh, do you see
what I see?

04:39.179 --> 04:40.177
Come on!

04:44.116 --> 04:45.150
Locked.

04:45.152 --> 04:47.818
We can get in
through that air vent.

04:50.923 --> 04:51.856
[clanks]

04:54.827 --> 04:56.127
Let's check out
that console.

04:57.896 --> 04:59.196
Snakes.

04:59.198 --> 05:01.299
Yow!

05:01.301 --> 05:03.100
Don't let that
one get away.

05:05.937 --> 05:07.071
Gotcha!

05:07.073 --> 05:09.808
Don't tell me snakes
stole all this stuff.

05:09.810 --> 05:11.742
Well, it would explain why
that piece of equipment

05:11.744 --> 05:14.645
seemed to be moving
under its own power.

05:14.647 --> 05:17.381
What do you think,
Leonardo?

05:17.383 --> 05:19.016
Uh, Leonardo?

05:19.018 --> 05:22.053
Did you ever notice what
intricate craftsmanship

05:22.055 --> 05:23.321
these old buildings have?

05:23.323 --> 05:24.989
Craftsmanship?

05:24.991 --> 05:26.957
Will you get down
from there?

05:26.959 --> 05:28.226
We've got work to do!

05:28.228 --> 05:30.628
Uh, I'd really rather not.

05:30.630 --> 05:33.531
Oh, come on,
quit clowning around.

05:34.899 --> 05:37.702
This must be one of the snakes
that was stolen from the zoo.

05:37.704 --> 05:40.438
Stolen snake stealing
electronic equipment?

05:40.440 --> 05:41.472
Makes sense to me.

05:41.474 --> 05:43.074
But what would snakes want

05:43.076 --> 05:45.243
with all these
high-tech gizmos?

05:45.245 --> 05:48.046
Well, obviously they aren't
doing it for themselves.

05:48.048 --> 05:51.883
Someone must be using some
form of snake mind control.

05:51.885 --> 05:53.384
[gagging]

05:53.386 --> 05:54.485
What's the matter,
Leonardo?

05:54.487 --> 05:56.387
Oh, nothing,

05:56.389 --> 05:57.856
just a slight headache.

05:57.858 --> 06:01.091
Whoa, this scaly, little
dude sure wants to go home.

06:01.093 --> 06:03.894
It must be under
a thought control command

06:03.896 --> 06:05.796
to return with the others.

06:05.798 --> 06:08.098
If we can slip
on this homing device,

06:08.100 --> 06:10.501
we can follow it back
to its base of operations,

06:10.503 --> 06:12.670
and catch the mastermind
behind all of this.

06:12.672 --> 06:14.004
Leave it to Donatello

06:14.006 --> 06:16.174
to have a homing device
that fits a snake.

06:16.176 --> 06:19.143
Okay, Raphael,
you help out.

06:19.145 --> 06:20.879
[hissing]

06:20.881 --> 06:22.146
There!
Now let him go.

06:25.551 --> 06:27.451
Okay, let's follow it.

06:30.256 --> 06:32.390
[sighs]
This is gonna
be a long night.

06:34.559 --> 06:36.394
[Vernon]
April? It's late.

06:36.396 --> 06:38.763
I'm tired,
and I want to go home.

06:38.765 --> 06:40.064
Come on, Vernon.

06:40.066 --> 06:42.099
Where's your
journalistic spirit?

06:42.101 --> 06:44.168
We've got to pin down
this missing snake story.

06:44.170 --> 06:45.203
[glass smashing]

06:45.205 --> 06:46.337
What was that?

06:48.406 --> 06:51.609
[April]
Somebody's breaking into
that sporting goods store.

06:51.611 --> 06:53.978
Oh, I hope
they don't see us.

06:53.980 --> 06:55.880
I just hope
we can see them.

06:57.316 --> 07:00.251
Okay, boys, you know
what the orders are.

07:00.253 --> 07:01.986
We gotta swipe
some diving gear.

07:01.988 --> 07:03.388
Right, Pinky.

07:09.127 --> 07:11.862
Leave us get out of here
before the cops arrive.

07:11.864 --> 07:13.898
It's Pinky McFingers.

07:13.900 --> 07:15.066
This is great!

07:15.068 --> 07:18.169
Oh, yeah, swell.
I have to go now.

07:18.171 --> 07:19.737
Stay put, Vernon.

07:19.739 --> 07:21.205
This is news.

07:21.207 --> 07:23.574
[April]
Hmm. Since when
are those hoodlums

07:23.576 --> 07:25.476
into aquatic sports?

07:27.846 --> 07:29.046
He's up to something,

07:29.048 --> 07:31.249
and we're going
to find out what it is.

07:31.251 --> 07:32.884
Must we?

